com.google.cloud

Interface Page<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the value type that the page holds
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AsyncPage<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AsyncPageImpl, PageImpl, QueryResult

    public interface Page<T>
    Interface for Google Cloud paginated results.

    Use Page to iterate through all values (also in next pages): 

     Page<T> page = ...; // get a Page<T> instance
 Iterator<T> iterator = page.iterateAll();
 while (iterator.hasNext()) {
   T value = iterator.next();
   // do something with value
 }

    Or handle pagination explicitly: 

     Page<T> page = ...; // get a Page<T> instance
 while (page != null) {
   for (T value : page.values()) {
     // do something with value
   }
   page = page.nextPage();
 }

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Iterator<T> iterateAll()
      Returns an iterator for all values, possibly also in the next pages.
      Page<T> nextPage()
      Returns the next page of results or null if no more result.
      String nextPageCursor()
      Returns the cursor for the nextPage or null if no more results.
      Iterable<T> values()
      Returns the values contained in this page.
